item.title: One last problem!
item.dc:creator: @drubrkletern drubrkletern
item.description:
@drubrkletern wrote:

Loveandpower:

@drub sometimes it doesn’t work on 64 bit computers that are windows 7 like that for some reason. You can enter a client and login after like 2-3 steps you log out. I had a friend who had that issue on my client.

How?

The thing wrong is that it cannot find your java executable, so just find your jre folder, then simply direct the batch to that executable.

item.title: One last problem!
item.dc:creator: @drubrkletern drubrkletern
item.description:
@drubrkletern wrote:

you dont need an bat to exe converter; simply edit the batch contents from something like C:/program files/java/jre/bin/java.exe
to something like C:/program files(x86)/java/jre/bin/java.exe
